Your `axios.post` can take in 3 arguments. The first one is the endpoint, second is the payload, and the third is the config or where your token is stored. 

`axios.post(endpoint, payload, config)`

I think you have it set in the wrong order:

```
axios
    .post(&quot;https://example.com&quot;, {
      headers: {
        token:
          &quot;abc&quot;
      },
      solutions: {
        solution: answer
      }
    })
```

this should be:

```
axios
    .post(&quot;https://example.com&quot;, 
      solutions: {
        solution: answer
      },
      {
         headers: {
           token: &quot;abc&quot;
         }
      }
     )
